It exits with a success return code, however, it does not push anything into the local docker-daemon registry.  The output of a subsequent `docker image ls` remains unchanged.  My 
expectation is that I would see a `climo2:latest` image in there.

There is no useful `dockerd` output in `sudo journalctl -f` while the copy is running.

The `dockerd` version is 24.0.5.  I have also tried 24.08 and 23.08 with the same result.  I have tried it on NixOS and Ubuntu.  I've also tried the same thing after upgrading skopeo to 1.14.1
